{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Street lighting is at risk of being restricted once again to residences and neighborhoods able to afford it.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by Virginia Tech history Prof A Roger Ekirch notes that cities and towns across the United States are contemplating significantly reducing the number of street lamps to lower their hefty electric bills; argues that aside from very real concerns about the impact on crime, the absence of street lighting will make people more likely to stay at home at night, decreasing an appreciation for the night and diminishing the quality of the communities.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "5", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"lastname": "EKIRCH", "rank": 1, "firstname": "A.", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "Roger"}], "original": "By A. ROGER EKIRCH", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/08/opinion/sunday/as-streetlights-vanish-a-return-to-a-darker-age.html", "lead_paragraph": "Street lighting is at risk of being restricted once again to residences and neighborhoods able to afford it.", "headline": {"seo": "As Streetlights Vanish, a Return to a Darker Age", "main": "Return to a Darker Age", "print_headline": "Return to a Darker Age", "content_kicker": "Opinion", "kicker": "Opinion"}, "_id": "53f23b2838f0d847437df788", "word_count": "844", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2012/01/08/sunday-review/08DARK/08DARK-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2012/01/08/sunday-review/08DARK/08DARK-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 415, "url": "images/2012/01/08/sunday-review/08DARK/08DARK-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2012/01/08/sunday-review/08DARK/08DARK-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "415"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2012/01/08/sunday-rev